==INTRODUCTION==
	vimrc is a file where you can set custom settings/overrides for your vim environment. Here's mine. 
==GETTING THINGS GOING==
 - save this file as a hidden .vimrc under your home directory

 	OR

 - clone this repo at a convinient location in your file system. create a soft link called ".vimrc" that points to the vimrc file in the cloned repo.
 - restart vim
